In introductory physics textbooks, the standard basis vectors are often denoted formula_32 instead (or formula_33, in which the hat symbol formula_34 typically denotes unit vectors). In this case, the scalar and vector components are denoted respectively &quot;ax&quot;, &quot;ay&quot;, &quot;az&quot;, and a&quot;x&quot;, a&quot;y&quot;, a&quot;z&quot; (note the difference in boldface). Thus,

